--- RUN: jma/fetch_jma_monthly.py (help)
CMD: python3 jma/fetch_jma_monthly.py --help
usage: fetch_jma_monthly.py [-h] [--station {mikuni,fukui,katsuyama}]
                            [--prec-no PREC_NO] [--block-no BLOCK_NO]
                            [--page {hourly_s1,hourly_a1}]
                            [--station-name STATION_NAME] --year YEAR
                            [--month MONTH] [--start-month START_MONTH]
                            [--end-month END_MONTH] [--output-dir OUTPUT_DIR]
                            [--sleep SLEEP] [--timeout TIMEOUT]
                            [--retries RETRIES] [--force]

Fetch JMA hourly data by scraping HTML table pages

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --station {mikuni,fukui,katsuyama}
                        Station preset (auto-sets prec-no, block-no, page)
  --prec-no PREC_NO     JMA prefecture code (e.g. 57)
  --block-no BLOCK_NO   JMA block code (e.g. 47631, 1226)
  --page {hourly_s1,hourly_a1}
                        hourly_s1 for main stations, hourly_a1 for AMeDAS
  --station-name STATION_NAME
                        Name prefix for output files
  --year YEAR
  --month MONTH         Single month (shorthand for --start/end-month)
  --start-month START_MONTH
  --end-month END_MONTH
  --output-dir OUTPUT_DIR
                        Output directory (default: jma/<station>_rawdata)
  --sleep SLEEP         Seconds between day requests
  --timeout TIMEOUT
  --retries RETRIES
  --force               Overwrite existing files
EXIT_CODE: 0

